    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Larvotto beach",
          "url": "https://goo.gl/maps/Aq3YPhCpPrtbfW3S7",
          "bold": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "A relatively large pebble beach. Like other Monaco beaches, it is heavily visited and among the most popular ones. You’ll find shops, ice cream stands, and toilets here. There is also a beach shower, as on most beaches."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Monte Carlo Harbour",
          "url": "https://goo.gl/maps/HizP4HUXYBM3Gaj57",
          "bold": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Taking a walk around the harbors in Monaco is also worth it. The most famous one is Monte Carlo Harbor, located below the aforementioned peninsula with the royal palace (which offers a nice view of the harbor). The harbor is home to the most luxurious yachts, and there’s plenty to see."
        }
      ]
    },
